{
  "stem": "8786.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So both of these shocks came simultaneously-- my arrival home and the same news.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he did not to tell my father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He did not to have my father should know it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He knew it, but he didn't want my father should know about it that he met some girls who were in Bergen-Belsen, and they told him, yes, that Greenfeld Nini or Mrs.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Greenfeld.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Yes, she passed away on the same day when the English army marched in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my brother was-- he just couldn't express his big joy by meeting me, because deep down he knew that there is-- there is plenty sad story behind it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so he stayed in Tornal'a.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And few days later, I think it was around Tisha B'Av-- which was summertime-- I did find out definitely that my mother and that my sisters did die.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was sitting shiva for one hour.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't-- I didn't even question the rabbinical authorities about it, because I know if you hear a-- a-- within 30 days, if you hear it, you have to sit shiva.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If it is more than 30 days, you only sit one hour-- that's the law.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I remember Tisha B'Av, it was anyway a sad day in our-- in our calendar.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was sitting alone.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't want my father to see me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was sitting shiva that time for the death of my mother.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, what should I tell you?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The town was they-- they tried to figure out who did survive, who did not survive.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the fact-- the bitter fact was that they had about 700 people before the war, 140-- 160 families, was totally about 700 people.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And now they survive about 125.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
